# Flex Living â€“ Reviews Dashboard

This project implements the Flex Living Developer Assessment: a reviews dashboard that helps managers monitor property performance, spot issues, and decide which guest reviews should appear on the public website.

---

## 1. Tech Stack

**Backend**

- Python 3.10
- FastAPI
- Uvicorn
- JSON files as data source (mock Hostaway + mock Google)

**Frontend**

- Plain HTML, CSS, JavaScript (no frameworks)
- Chart.js (via CDN) for simple charts
- LocalStorage for:
  - Approved reviews
  - Saved filter views
  - Internal review status and notes
  - Mock Google API keys

---

## 2. Project Structure

```text
backend/
  main.py                 # FastAPI app and API routes
  requirements.txt        # fastapi, uvicorn
  data/
    hostaway_mock.json    # Provided Hostaway reviews mock
    google_mock.json      # Mocked Google Places response

frontend/
  index.html              # Manager dashboard
  property.html           # Property details + public reviews section
  css/
    styles.css            # Main dashboard / property styling
    google_admin.css      # Styling for Google API key admin page
  js/
    dashboard.js          # All dashboard logic (filters, charts, approvals, etc.)
    property.js           # Loads approved reviews for a single property
    google_admin.js       # Google API key management (mocked)
  admin/
    google.html           # Google API key management UI
